what is the best way to launder a baseball cap without damaging the bill suggestion department stores such as walmart of kmart sell frames or what look like a skeleton of a hat you place your hat on top of this frame when washing them and it keeps your hat from getting stretched our and bent suggestion i always throw my husbands hats in the washer without a frame though and afterward i place the hat on the bottom side of a small kitchen pot it keeps the hat in good form suggestion i have read that you can wash your hat by placing in on the top rack of your dish washer it keeps the hat in one spot but the water soap and water pressure do a good job at cleaning off the grime i have not ever tried this myself but it may be worth a try just remember that no matter how you wash it is never to be dried in the dryer or it may loose it shape size and color good luck Textile manufacturing Washing machine Hat Cookware and bakeware Dishwashing Laundry Menstrual cup Wal-Mart Mattress Dishwasher Car washing techniques Dry cleaning Bonsai Japanese toilet Toilet Sears Holdings Corporation Kitchen Billiards Brewery Customs and etiquette of Japan Japanese tea ceremony Whose Line Is It Anyway? Clown Sento Poker jargon Snooker Knife Kosher foods Spark plug Soap bubble Headgear Top-bar hive Coffee Tattoo Bong Wok Collecting fossils Gravity Clinker (boat building) Leather Clothing Cruising (maritime) Tofu Eight ball Manicure Tibetan people Mario Fecal incontinence Chili con carne Pottery Pittsburgh Steelers Baseball Haggis Hard water Seismic retrofit Sushi Professional wrestling holds Soap Cheating in poker Horse One Piece minor characters Characters in the Smurfs Tea Classics Equine conformation Hygiene Common bean Japanese cuisine Screen-printing Professional wrestling throws Bottle Wario Dollar store New England Patriots Department store Sponge Laundry detergent Diseases of the honeybee Hat-trick Basement Lake Detergent Hamster Bento Washboard 2004 World Series Screw Hand washing Pow